TKINTER:

    Buttons:
        - If using the tkinter library and you want to execute a command use 'command=lambda: [COMMAND]', so it will only execute if I press the button
        - with .grid(sticky="nsew") the button will fill one place

    Text:
        - to get the text input use .get("0.1", "end-1c")

    Entry:
        - to get teh text input use .get()

    Label:
        - to change text use .configure(text="") (also works with font etc)

    Option Menu:
        - to create one use OptionMenu
        - u need a StringVar and a *list as parameters
        - to check it changes use .trace("w", [command])
        - to not cause any errors use *args in the function/methode


Tkmacosx:
    (look at https://github.com/Saadmairaj/tkmacosx#requirements)

    look for SaveVar (could be useful)

    Button:
        - for hover effect use 'overbackground' and 'overforeground'

